CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 6, 1958, pg. 4, reads: "Cars Collide, Burn, Three Hurt - When the smaller car, right photo, being driven by Preston Perkins, of 405 Dinwiddie St., at Chauncey St. and Wylie Ave., ran into the car, in left photo, between 3:30 and 4 A. M., Thanksgiving, being driven by Jeffie Johnson, of 2726 Bedford Ave., Johnson's car caught fire and was completely demolished. The fire also burned Perkins' car.  Both drivers and Wilbert Ramsey, a passenger in the Johnson car, received treatment for minor injuries at Mercy Hospital and were released. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pontiac car belonging to Jeffie Johnson with crumpled left side and hood, parked in snowy lot with other damaged automobiles, chain link fence, and manufacturing buildings in background
